<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.logging.LogManager.Constructor" Title="Constructor method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogManager">LogManager</PageRef> ->
    Constructor
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>LogManager</TypeRef> constructor creates a manager with no log targets and a manager-level include severity filter of <TypeRef>SeverityFilter::All</TypeRef>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Note Type="Important">
      <Paragraph>
        A newly constructed manager has no output destinations. Add at least one target with <PageRef PageName="cobalt.logging.LogManager.AddLogTarget">AddLogTarget</PageRef> before expecting messages to be written anywhere.
      </Paragraph>
    </Note>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[LogManager();]]></Code>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
    <PageRefList>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.logging.LogManager">LogManager</PageRefListEntry>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.logging.LogManager.AddLogTarget">LogManager.AddLogTarget</PageRefListEntry>
    </PageRefList>
  </Section>
</XMLDocContent>
